Name: poly(vinyl alcohol)
Reference: Xue, Guobin; Zhong, Jiang; Gao, Shu; Wang, Bo , Carbon , 96 , 871-878 (2016)
Remarks: [PVA] purchased from Sinopharm Chemical Reagent Co., Ltd. (China), DP=1788 (reported), [rGO] graphite (460mesh, purity>99.5%) oxidizad to graphene oxide (GO) via modified Hummer's method, then GO dispersion in water reduced with hydrazine hydrate (1/1 mass ratio to GO) at 95C for 8h
Morphology: Thickness of rGO nanosheets in the composite=6-28nm (TEM), free vol. size (Vf)=ca.68.3(angstrom)**3, fractional free vol. (fr)=ca.9.22% (PALS, taken from the Fig.3a, c)
Mixing / Blending method: PVA/water soln. mixed with aq. dispersion of GO at 95C for 0.5h, hydrazine hydrate (1/1 mass ratio to GO) added to the PVA/GO mixt. and GO in situ reduced by heating at 95C for 8h, finally water removed by freeze-drying from the PVA/rGO soln.
Other 1st structure info: Interfacial interaction between rGO and PVA chains observed in the composite (FTIR)

Name: poly(vinylidene fluoride)
Reference: Zhang, Wen-bin; Zhang, Zhi-xing; Yang, Jing-hui; Huang, Ting; Zhang, Nan; Zheng, Xiao-tong; Wang, Yong; Zhou, Zuo-wan , Carbon , 90 , 242-254 (2015)
Remarks: [poly(vinylidene fluoride)(PVDF)]Kynar 720, MFR=22.8g/10min(230C, 3.8kg), density=1.78g/cm3, obtained from Arkema(France), [carbon nanotube(CNT)]carboxyl content ca.0.51wt%, outer diameter>50nm, length=ca.10-30micron, purity=ca.90%, obtained from Chengdu Institute of Organic Chemistry, Chinese Academy of Science(China)
[proc] Compression: compression molded at 200C and 10MPa for ca.8min, then cold-compression molded at 23C and 20MPa for 20min
Mixing / Blending method: PVDF/DMF solution and CNT/DMF solution sonicated at 80C for 20min respectively, then two solutions mixed and further sonicated at 80C for 1h, then solution temperature raised to 120C for ca.2h to remove most of the solvent, residual solvent removed at 70C for more than 24h

Mixing / Blending method: PVDF/DMF solution, CNT/DMF solution and GO/DMF solution sonicated at 80C for 20min respectively, then three solutions mixed and further sonicated at 80C for 1h, then solution temperature raised to 120C for ca.2h to remove most of the solvent, residual solvent removed at 70C for more than 24h
